#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:99
msgid "Variation Swatches — card image swap"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:100
msgid "On shop / archive pages, clicking a swatch swaps the product card image to the matching variation image — no navigation, no Quick View."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:107
msgid "Variation Swatches — image swatches"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:108
msgid "Lets each attribute term use an uploaded image instead of a colour; adds the upload UI to the term-edit screen and renders image thumbnails in the shop picker and PDP buy box. Image wins over colour when both are set."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:115
msgid "Variation Swatches — hover tooltip"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:116
msgid "Shows a CSS hover tooltip on colour and image swatches; the text defaults to the term name and is overridable per term from the term-edit screen."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:123
msgid "Variation Swatches — auto colour sampler"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:124
msgid "Samples each variation image to a representative hex (cached as post-meta, refreshed on save, pre-warmed via WP-Cron) and uses it as the swatch colour when no manual term colour is set. One toggle drives both the sampler pipeline and the render-path fallback."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:131
msgid "Variation Swatches — WPC Bundles / FBT compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:132
msgid "Forwards all buy-box form fields to WooCommerce's add-to-cart endpoint so WPC Product Bundles and WPC Frequently-Bought-Together hidden inputs reach the cart; exposes a JS flag for the runtime."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:139
msgid "Design panel"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:140
msgid "Adds a ShopOS → Design admin page to set a store accent + a few core design tokens (colours, corner radius) that flow to every module. Off = no page and no CSS; even on, only tokens you change are emitted."
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:147
msgid "Perf probe — diagnostic response headers"
msgstr ""

#: src/Core/Feature_Flags.php:148
msgid "When on, storefront requests carrying ?shopos_perf=1 respond with X-ShopOS-Queries / X-ShopOS-Render-Ms / X-ShopOS-Mem-MB headers, read by the tools/perf-budget.php per-template budget check. Off = no listeners, no headers. Numbers only — nothing sensitive."
msgstr ""

